parameters:
Would you like to see today's performance? Please wait just
a little longer.

Shichijuro-san is the star actor of this theater. He's so
popular that there are women who come to the playhouse just
to see him, even from outside of Edo.

Shichijuro-san, I'm glad to hear that your child was born
safely. It seems you've even improved your dancing skills
further.

You can only see Shichirou-san's play here! Come on, come
on, please proceed to the back~

Miss, this is the staff entrance. If you want to watch the
performance, please enter from the front.
No! I can't take it anymore! The customers are waiting!

Thank you so much for last time. Thanks to all of you, we
were able to continue the performance without any issues.

What?! Are you serious?! The audience has already entered
and is waiting!

I'm terribly sorry, Manager... However, if something were to
happen to Oei, I would regret it. Please, allow me to return
home for a while.

Even so... The entrance has already started, and if we
suddenly suspend the performance, the audience will get
angry... It would ruin the theater's reputation, you know?
But... I cannot back down. My family's life is at stake...
Excuse me... Is something the matter?
--Whoa! Young lady, did you hear our conversation?
Yes, I'm sorry. About suspending the performance or not...

I couldn't help but overhear. Actually, today is the
expected delivery date for my wife, Oei. But the midwife
said it might be a difficult birth, and I'm worried, so I
want to go back home and watch over my wife--

I understand the feeling of caring for your family, but a
lot of customers are waiting in front of the stage for your
play. Please perform. I'm begging you, Kisanosuke-san!

I see. It's such an important reason. Understood. It must be
fate that I passed by-- if it's alright with you, I'll take
the stage!

What?! What are you saying?! What can a plain girl like you
do? This isn't a playground. This is a prestigious theater!

Hmph! I'm not a plain girl, you know? My name is Karin. I
can do movements like this.

Wow, what a leap! Are you an acrobat or something? That's an
incredible physical ability!

Hmm. With this, maybe we can entrust the stage to you.
Karin-san, may we ask you to buy us some time?

Yes! I'll call my friends and keep the performance going
until the birth is safely over. Kisanosuke-san, please hurry
to your home.

Thank you, Karin-san. Then I'll leave the stage in your
hands and return to my wife at home. Excuse me--

...So that's why I called the two of you, but can I count on
you to help buy some time on stage?

What a sudden request? Weren't we supposed to be searching
for a weapon to defeat demons?

I'm sorry! But they were in trouble, so I had to ask!
Yugiri-chan, Momiji-san, please stand on stage with me.
Please!
I don't mind, but what kind of play are we going to perform?

Well... How about a gripping battle drama? Our strength lies
in fighting after all...

A sword dance? This is a traditional Kabuki theater. If we
perform a clumsy and poor act like one from a cheap
playhouse, the audience will boo us?

How about [Thief versus Kunoichi in Hiding]? Karin-chan and
Yugiri-san could chase each other around on stage and
ultimately have a duel...
～～! Momiji-dono, you shouldn't say such things...!

That's brilliant, Momiji-san! It sounds interesting! Let's
definitely do it!

(I guess there's no choice but to go along with this
play...)

Is the discussion over? Then all three of you, quickly to
the stage! If we keep the audience waiting too long, there
might be a riot!

Understood, Manager-san. Let's hurry and change then head to
the stage!

Karin: ...Yugiri, we two are official government spies,
aren't we? If we do something conspicuous in a place where
the sun shines, it defeats the purpose of being covert
agents, doesn't it? Are we really going to stand in front of
a large audience?

No need to worry! If we cover our mouths, our identities
won't be revealed!

Sigh... Understood. There's no more time, right? Let's
complete this play with the resolve of jumping off the stage
at Kiyomizu...
If the two of you are fighting, what should I do?

Momiji-san will become a stagehand and make up the story
appropriately. Don't worry, it'll work out!
...(I wonder if it'll really be okay...)
--The three of them changed and headed to the stage!

Hey, how long do you plan to keep us waiting?! It's already
been half an hour since the play was supposed to start?
Is Shichijuro-sama not appearing yet? Show us quickly!

Um... I apologize. Shichijuro-san is taking time to prepare,
so the three of us will perform the play. Please forgive us.

Is this like a prelude? We came to see Shichijuro-sama's
play...

Then, let's begin [Thief versus Kunoichi in Hiding]. Please
listen quietly--
Welcome to the dance hall. The entrance fee is 1000 mon.\$
Yes, thank you. Please come in.

I lined up early in the morning to see Shichijuro-sama's
dance performance. I wonder what kind of theme today's stage
will have? I'm truly looking forward to it♪
